        "title": "How to specify query in sqlite with min() function",
        "body": "<p>I have table defined by code below<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>CREATE TABLE Products\n(\nP_Id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\nname TEXT,\nprice REAL,\nsellPrice REAL,\nplu INTEGER,\ncodeBar TEXT,\ntax INTEGER,\namount INTEGER,\ndate TEXT\n);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>and when I try to execute query like that I get a syntax error (it's a prepared statement)<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>select * \nfrom Products \nwhere P_Id = min(select P_Id from Products where codeBar=?);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Can somebody please help? What is wrong with this query?<\/p>\n\n<p>The exact error message I get is:<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p><em>java.sql.SQLException: near \"select\": syntax error<\/em><\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>Thx for help.<\/p>\n",
